# Front-end Styling & HTML Rules

## CSS/SCSS Methodology

- Always use **SCSS** for styling.
- Follow the **BEM (Block Element Modifier)** methodology for class naming.
- **Modifier Syntax**: Use a single underscore `_` for modifiers instead of the standard `--`.
  - Example: `.button_active`, `.card_theme_dark`.
- **Nesting**: Always use SCSS nesting with the ampersand `&` operator to maintain BEM structure.
  - Example:
    ```scss
    .block-name {
      &__element {
        // styles
      }
      &_modifier {
        // styles
      }
    }
    ```

## HTML Structure & Class Naming

- **Independent Components**: If a component or markup section contains an independent functional unit, do NOT nest it under the parent's BEM classes. Instead, create a new standalone class (a new BEM Block).
  - **Incorrect**: `<div class="parent__card">` (if the card is a separate entity).
  - **Correct**:
    ```html
    <div class="parent-class">
      <div class="parent-class__col-1">
        <div class="card">
          <div class="card__image"></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    ```
- Avoid deep nesting that doesn't follow BEM (no more than 3 levels if possible, keeping it flat via `&__`).

## Accessibility (A11y) — Mandatory

- **ARIA Attributes**: Always include necessary ARIA attributes for interactive and non-semantic elements.
  - Use `aria-label` or `aria-labelledby` for buttons, links, and inputs that lack visible text.
  - Use `aria-expanded`, `aria-hidden`, `aria-controls`, and `aria-selected` where appropriate to describe state.
- **Roles**: Explicitly define `role="..."` if the element's function is not clear from its tag (e.g., `role="tablist"`, `role="dialog"`).
- **Images**: Every `<img>` tag must have an `alt` attribute. Use `alt=""` for decorative images or descriptive text for meaningful ones.
- **Forms**: Ensure every form input has a corresponding `<label>` or an `aria-label`.
- **Focus Management**: Ensure interactive elements are keyboard-accessible and have visible focus states.

## Technical Implementation

- Ensure all new styles are written in `.scss` files.
- When generating HTML, prioritize semantic tags while strictly adhering to the "independent component" rule for classes.
